University of Kentucky lost 71-64 to the University of Wisconsin Badgers in Saturday night's NCAA tournament semi-final game . 
  The Wildcats will now face off against Duke in the final on Monday - their first final since 1941  . 
  More than a thousand University of Kentucky fans gathered near the school's Lexington campus Saturday night to celebrate the loss . 
  Police in riot gear arrested 31 people on charges of public intoxication and disorderly conduct  . 
  The Wildcats were kicked out of the tournament for being the first undefeated team in NCAA history . 
  Wisconsin will now play Duke in Monday's final . 
 